description: Barcelona have won their last three matches against Real Madrid in all competitions, only once in the entire history of ElClásico, between 2008 and 2010 under Josep Guardiola, have the Blaugrana managed 4+ consecutive wins. description: Sevilla have won seven and drawn just one of their last eight LaLiga matches against UD Las Palmas, their longest unbeaten run against the Canary Islands side in their history in the top-flight. Prior to this run, the Gran Canaria side had won seven of their last 14 away games against Sevilla in the competition.

title: Real Valladolid vs Girona - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 36
description: Real Valladolid have won both of their home matches against Girona in LaLiga, both 1-0. Only against three teams have the Valladolid side won their first three home matches without conceding in the top-flight: Mallorca in 1983, Cádiz in 1986, and Alaves in 1998. After their victory in the reverse fixture in December 2024, Girona can win back-to-back matches against Real Valladolid in all competitions for the second time in history, having achieved this feat between 2015 and 2016 in LaLiga Hypermotion.

description: Algiers is hosting one of the most passionate football derbies. The passion that this match gives off throughout the city is incredible. The history, the culture, the anecdotes are told through this documentary, the derby of Algiers is more than a game.

title: Stadium of Fears
description: Everyone knows the biggest stadiums in the world. But sometimes its the smallest stadiums that are the most intimidating for players, due to their fans and their fervor. Several big names in football tell you about their experiences in these stadiums where it can sometimes be difficult to play.

title: Imene, The Lady of the Noble Art

She has become a symbol of perseverance, a testament to the power of determination in the face of adversity. This documentary tells the battle against poverty and a bold defiance. description: Rennes have won only three of their 19 meetings against Nice over the last 10 seasons in Ligue 1 but have won the last two at home. title: Montpellier vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2024/25 Week 33

title: Ligue 1 legends (Barthez + Nasri) MARSEILLE PREVIOUS STARS Barthez + Nasri
description: Many legends have had unforgettable competitions in French stadiums. In this program, we show you their best moments.

title: Villarreal vs Leganes - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 36
description: Villarreal have won six of their nine LaLiga matches against Leganes, including their most recent 5-2 win at Butarque in December 2024. They could achieve a league double against the Madrid side in the same campaign for the second time in the competition, having also achieved it in 2018/19. This will be the fifth meeting at La Cerámica between Villarreal and CD Leganes in LaLiga, with the Villarreal side achieving three wins and Leganes one, with all four by the same scoreline: 2-1.

title: Holstein Kiel vs Freiburg - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: SC Freiburg and Holstein Kiel have only previously met twice in professional football. The Storks won 2-1 at home in the second round of the 2018/19 DFB-Pokal, while Freiburg secured a 3-2 home victory earlier this season. SC Freiburg have only won one of their last seven Bundesliga games away at league debutants : 2-1 at Greuther Furth in May 2013. They have lost each of their last three such fixtures, scoring two goals and conceding nine. Their most recent trip to a top-flight debutant saw them lose 3-2 in Heidenheim last season.

title: Bayern Munchen vs Borussia Monchengladbach - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: FC Bayern Munchen have won three consecutive Bundesliga games against Borussia Monchengladbach for the first time since between 2013 and 2014. They have only ever put together a longer winning run against the Foals across their opening five top-flight meetings from 1965 to 1967. Overall, no other side in league history has as many wins against FCB as Gladbach do. FC Bayern Munchen are German champions for the 34th time. It means they will end the season having topped the table for 32 of the 34 matchdays, something they last managed in 2012/13 under Jupp Heynckes. FCB have lost only two of their first 32 Bundesliga matches this season, something they last achieved in 2016/17 under Carlo Ancel

title: Bayer Leverkusen vs Borussia Dortmund - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: After winning the reverse fixture, Bayer 04 Leverkusen could now do a league double over Borussia Dortmund for the first time since 2006/07. However, their three-game wait at home for a victory against BVB in the Bundesliga is currently their longest against any top-flight side. Bayer 04 Leverkusen are unbeaten in their last seven Bundesliga games – only Union Berlin are currently enjoying a longer undefeated spell. However, B04’s 2-2 draw in Freiburg was their third draw in their last four games and their 11th overall in 2024/25, a joint league high together with RB Leipzig. Since 2000, the Werkself have only ever shared the points more often in a season in 2009/10.

title: Bundesliga - Special 2024/2025 Best of April
description: The Best of April. It’s the business end of the season, crunch time in the Bundesliga. Nothing is decided yet! Sports psychology knows it’s down to mental strength now... In the chase for Europe. Staying in the league and holding your nerve to beat the drop.

title: Stuttgart vs Augsburg - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: VfB Stuttgart are unbeaten in their last seven competitive games against FC Augsburg, winning each of the last four without conceding a single goal. VfB won the most recent meeting 1-0 at home in the quarter-finals of the DFB-Pokal on 4th February 2025. Only FC Bayern have created more big chances this season than VfB Stuttgart, whereas FC Augsburg have had the fewest in the league – not even half as many as VfB.

title: Eintracht Frankfurt vs St. Pauli - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: Eintracht Frankfurt, founded in 1899, are now set to play their 1,899th Bundesliga game. They are still unbeaten in their six home matches against St. Pauli and have only hosted RB Leipzig more often in the top flight without ever losing. Eintracht Frankfurt are unbeaten in their last 14 Bundesliga games against promoted sides, winning each of the last four. They now have the chance to equal two club records: a five-game winning streak against promoted teams from 1991 under Dragoslav Stepanovic and a 15-match undefeated run against them between 2008 and 2012.

title: Bundesliga - Special 2024/2025 Best of April
description: The Best of April. It’s the business end of the season, crunch time in the Bundesliga. Nothing is decided yet! Sports psychology knows it’s down to mental strength now... In the chase for Europe. Staying in the league and holding your nerve to beat the drop.

title: Wolfsburg vs Hoffenheim - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 33
description: TSG Hoffenheim and VfL Wolfsburg meet for the third time this season. The Wolves won 3-0 at home in the DFB-Pokal round of 16 at the start of December and also beat TSG 1-0 in Sinsheim in the reverse fixture. VfL could now win three competitive games against the same side in a single season for just the fourth time in professional football. TSG Hoffenheim sit in 15th place having only collected 31 points from 32 games this season – they have only ever claimed fewer points from 32 Bundesliga matchdays in 2012/13. TSG are five points clear of 16th place – since the introduction of three points per win, only 1. FC Nurnberg in 1998/99 have ever blown such an advantage this late on in a season.

title: Al Ahli (KSA) vs Kawasaki (JPN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2024/25 - Final

Al-Ahli have won only once in 5 matches against East Asian teams, with the win against Shenzhen 2-1 in the 2005 quarter-finals. This will be the fourth final between a Saudi team and a Japanese team in the AFC Champions League elite, the most common final matchup in the tournament. title: Bundesliga Special 2024/25 - Der Klassiker Unseen
description: Der Klassiker as you’ve never seen it before: FC Bayern Munchen against Borussia Dortmund from a radically different perspective. This 26-minute Bundesliga Special takes us behind the scenes and out onto the pitch itself. Referee Tobias Welz, kitted out with RefCam and microphone, brings the viewers right into the heart of the action. Offering an up-close taste of the pulsating, and occasionally heated, exchanges with players and coaches, as well as the intensive communication with the fourth official and VAR. What’s going on behind the scenes, in the referees’ changing room and also at the Video Assistant Centre in Cologne?

title: My Faith in Sport - Sawm
description: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab. Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan.

title: The Outdoor Sports Show 2025
description: Welcome to this episode of Outdoor Sports Show, the TV magazine programme which takes you to the best events and introduces you to the characters from the action-packed world of outdoor sports. We strongly believe that from the many different paths we take in life, some of them must be dirt paths, because filling our lives with adventure gives us some great stories to share and this is what the outdoor sports show will bring to you!We now travel to the United Arab Emirates for another marathon. Staged under the auspices of the Dubai Sports Council, the Dubai Marathon celebrated its 24th anniversary with thousands of runners taking to the area around the iconic Burj Al Arab. We stay in the U

title: World Sailing Show 2025
description: The World Sailing Show 2025 brings you the most thrilling moments from elite sailing competitions around the globe. From high-speed foiling action to tactical offshore battles, this episode covers top events like the America’s Cup, SailGP, and The Ocean Race. Meet the world’s best sailors, explore cutting-edge boat technology, and witness the drama of high-stakes racing on the water.
